<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-08"><hi rend="italic">June 8, 1900</hi></date>.
                                (Received June 11.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Paotingfu missionaries safe up to the present. Chinese Government has
                            sent troops and promises ample protection, but this does not insure
                            permanent safety. Impossible to send foreign relief from forces now
                            here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>